  "commentary": "With SPX at 6600.32 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-9.6B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+16.6B), dealers are currently in a neutral hedging posture but poised for significant flow depending on direction. The massive GEX surge (3435% 1-min change) and recent regime flip into PIN suggests dealers just shifted from short to long gamma, meaning they'll now provide liquidity by selling any push toward 6605-6610 resistance and buying any dip toward 6590 support. Key inflection points are 6590 (where dealer buying accelerates) and the 6621 GEX flip level above which the regime could reverse back to negative gamma.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 6590-6610 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
